text:
Expensive satay at 0.90 per stick, taste is so-so. If priced at 0.70 cents per stick then reasonable for being at hawker and its subpar taste.

They don’t issue buzzer, after ordering I have to walk far back and forth 2 times to check on my order. The 2nd time I just wait there for it. The lady at the counter didn’t mention any specific time, just say wait and come back later, so I went to check at 15 minutes interval.

My order, placed at 7:46 PM as shown on the receipt, was initially supposed to be ready in 20 minutes. I returned at 8:20 PM only to be informed the satay order was incorrect and I would need to wait longer. Considering the high price of 90 cents per piece, and my intention to sample every stall, this hour-long delay without any compensation has completely diminished my appetite. While it's a hawker stall, the poor service is still unacceptable.
DON'T TRY place .. there are better
Operate in coffeeshop so atmosphere is standard. The food is below average.
